[2] Pennsylvania
Date: Wed 25 Aug 2010
Source: VaccineNewsDaily.com, Philly.com report [edited]
<http://vaccinenewsdaily.com/news/214853-philadelphia-whooping-cough-cases-on-the-rise>


A rise in reported cases of pertussis in causing concern in the
greater Philadelphia area, health officials say. The suburban
counties of southeastern Pennsylvania have witnessed increased
occurrences of the infection, which can be fatal in infants,
Philly.com reports. Delaware County saw the largest increase in
cases, jumping from 5 cases to 44 within a 3 month period.

The 2nd highest increase in whooping cough cases was in Montgomery
County, Philly.com reports, where 39 new cases were tallied between
April and June 2010, compared to 8 new cases in the 3 months preceding.

[Byline: Malik Wilson]

