[4] California
Date: Mon 16 Aug 2010
Source: The Bakersfield Californian, Kern County Department of Public
Health Services (CA) [edited]
<http://www.bakersfield.com/news/local/x1415296021/Number-of-whooping-cough-cases-up-to-227>


An additional 17 cases of whooping cough were reported last week
[week of 9 Aug 2010] in Kern County, bringing the total to 227 for
2010, according to the Kern County Department of Public Health.

The monthly rate of cases of whooping cough, also known as pertussis,
in Kern County has been going up and up in 2010, though no deaths
have been reported. The weekly rate has, since 23 May 2010, ranged
from 5 between 30 May and 5 Jun 2010 to 33 between 27 Jun and 3 Jul
2010, according to Public Health. Of the 227 Kern cases, 182 were
reported in Bakersfield.

The reason for the uptick is unclear but it's happening across the
state so health officials are just trying to get the word out about
the need for vaccination, said Denise Smith, Public Health's
assistant director of disease control.

Officials have said the incidence of whooping cough is cyclical. In
Kern there were 6 reported cases in all of 2009 and 8 in 2008,
according to Public Health.

